### Current Setup Matches Official Documentation
The implementation exactly matches the Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide for Next.js:

```typescript
import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next';

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        {children}
        <SpeedInsights />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

### Additional Components
The project also has Vercel Analytics configured alongside Speed Insights:
- `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 is installed
- `<Analytics />` component is also present in the layout

## Next Steps for Deployment

To enable Speed Insights in production:

1. **Enable in Vercel Dashboard**
   - Navigate to your project in the Vercel dashboard
   - Go to Speed Insights section
   - Click "Enable" button
   - This adds routes at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*`

2. **Deploy to Vercel**
   - Run `vercel deploy` or push to your connected git repository
   - The tracking script will be automatically injected

3. **View Metrics**
   - After deployment and user visits, access Speed Insights from your project dashboard
   - Performance metrics will be available for analysis

